Open vSwitch is an open source OpenFlow capable virtual switch that is typically used with hypervisor 
to interconnect virtual machines withine a host and virtual machines between different hosts across 
networks. 

Features Include: 
1. VLAN tagging and 802.1q trunking
2. Standard spanning tree protocol(802.1D)
3. tunneling (e.g GRE, VXLAN, IPSEC)
4. QOS
